    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-09-10T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-09-10T00:00:00-05:00" n="456"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d456">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 861.48/680b</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Russian Ambassador</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_BBA1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Bakhmeteff</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-09-10">
                            <hi rend="italic">September 10, 1918</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">My Dear Mr. Ambassador</hi>: I am pleased to note your
                    willingness to transfer to the American Red Cross 150,000 pairs of shoes, for
                    the purpose of supplying the Czecho-Slovaks with footwear, and cordially approve
                    of this effort to relieve suffering and to aid in the common cause.</p>
                <p>Notification of your proposal has been sent to the American Red Cross, together
                    with a request that the Czecho-Slovaks be informed of the fact that these shoes
                    were furnished by the Russian Embassy in Washington.</p>
                <p>I am [etc.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_LR1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Robert Lansing</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
